title: Music of the Middle Ages 7
description:
Well, my children, I did as threatened and dug around in storage and came up with 22 more CD&#039;s of medieval music. Track information and cover art may therefore not be available for all of them. I went and checked at Amazon.com for each one to verify that they were out of print; some are available used, one was listed for SIXTY DOLLARS (!) and some simply didn&#039;t exist. These are lost treasures. Keep them well for me.

To save time and space, I ripped these at 320 kb rather than in Windows Lossless. As before, there are five torrents in total. This one includes:

Harmonia Mundi 1994 New Release Sampler
Officium (Jan Garbarek) <-- medieval Czech chants + modern saxophone = unique listening experience
Istampitta II (NY Ensemble for Early Music)
A Treasure Of Music For Hurdy-Gurdy (Rene Zosso ; Anne Osnowycz) <-- this was the $60 one

Be certain to download my other torrents of medieval and archaic music! Enjoy -- and keep seeding!

-- Rivenshield
